comments: Correctly called backcourt violation on CLE.
Turner (IND) firms up in his screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact.
Brogdon (IND) places his off-arm against Okoro (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as he releases and steps back.
Wade (CLE) moves toward Turner (IND) as they each attempt to establish rebounding position and marginal body contact occurs as Turner jumps underneath the basket.
Sabonis (IND) and Wade (CLE) make incidental arm contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Correctly called backcourt violation on CLE.
Okoro (CLE) and Brogdon (IND) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Holiday (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Allen's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact.
Allen (CLE) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the body contact made with Sabonis (IND) in the post.
Windler (CLE) is moving toward Sabonis (IND) when marginal body contact occurs as Sabonis is passing.
McConnell (IND) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Sexton (CLE) before any incidental arm or body contact occurs.
Brogdon (IND) and Windler (CLE) come together at the same spot in transition and Brogdon's off-arm is naturally releasing away when marginal contact occurs with Windler's front.
Allen's (CLE) hand is rested on Turner's (IND) back and marginal contact occurs as Turner moves to contest the shot attempt.
Replay review of the foul called on Turner (IND) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Turner turns into Windler (CLE) and makes body contact that affects Windler's shot attempt.
Sabonis (IND) grasps and then quickly releases Wade's (CLE) left arm during rebounding.
Sabonis (IND) is not established in Okoro's (CLE) path when he firms up on his left foot during the screen and he delivers contact to his side.
Okoro (CLE) and Brogdon (IND) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Okoro (CLE) attempts to commit a take foul on Sabonis (IND) and the contact is marginal.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact.
Okoro (CLE) brings his hands toward Brogdon's (IND) front and marginal contact occurs as Brogdon dribbles near the lane.
Brogdon (IND) does not releases the shot attempt prior to the expiration of the shot clock.
Sexton (CLE) brings his off-arm toward Sabonis' (IND) front and marginal contact occurs as Sexton naturally releases away.
Sabonis (IND) legally contests Sexton's (CLE) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Windler (CLE) and Sumner (IND) engage and disengage with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Brogdon (IND) and Okoro (CLE) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Okoro (CLE) commits a take foul on Brogdon (IND).
